ant of   Marston   with loss of <i>-r-</i>."]}]},{"name":"Nigel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of the medieval name <i>Nigellus</i>, a Latinized version (ostensibly representing a diminutive of Latin <i>niger</i> ‘black’) of the vernacular <i>Ni(h)el</i>, i.e.   Neil .  Although it is frequently found in medieval records, this form was probably not used in everyday life before its revival by antiquarians such as  Sir Walter  Scott in the 19th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Nigel de Merston was born in 1155, in Ampthill, Bedfordshire, England, his father, Albiri of Cainho, was 32 and his mother, Mrs Albini de Cainho, was 30. He had at least 2 sons with Isabella. He died on 3 February 1213, in England, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1155–3 February 1213":"1155–3. veebruar 1213","1155–1213":"1155–1213","1150–1235":"1150–1235","1173–1227":"1173–1227","1183–1227":"1183–1227","1123–Male":"1123–Surnud","1125–Female":"1125–Surnud","1227":"1227","1125":"1125","1235":"1235","1213":"1213","1145":"1145","1123":"1123","1155":"1155","3 February 1213":"3. veebruar 1213","1173":"1173","1183":"1183","1150":"1150","Ampthill, Bedfordshire, England":"Ampthill, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England","Ampthill, Bedford, England":"Ampthill, Bedfordshire, England","England":"England","Marston Moretaine, Bedfordshire, England":"Marston Moretaine, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1155–3 February 1213":"1155–3. helmikuuta 1213","1155–1213":"1155–1213","1150–1235":"1150–1235","1173–1227":"1173–1227","1183–1227":"1183–1227","1123–Male":"1123–Kuollut","1125–Female":"1125–Kuollut","1227":"1227","1125":"1125","1235":"1235","1213":"1213","1145":"1145","1123":"1123","1155":"1155","3 February 1213":"3. helmikuuta 1213","1173":"1173","1183":"1183","1150":"1150","Ampthill, Bedfordshire, England":"Ampthill, Bedfordshire,